1.8 "Financial Distress Event" denotes the occurrence of any one or more of the following circumstances regarding the specified party:

(a) The specified party ceases to operate as a going concern, fails to carry on business in the ordinary course, or becomes subject to any form of court-supervised reorganization or similar proceedings;

(b) A receiver, trustee, liquidator, or other similar agent is appointed for the specified party or its assets, not including a case where the specified party acts as a debtor-in-possession and continues to fulfill all its obligations under this Agreement;

(c) The specified party initiates, or has initiated, any proceedings under bankruptcy, insolvency, or debt relief law that have not been dismissed within ninety (90) days, regardless of whether the specified party is the filing party;

(d) The specified party enters into an agreement with its creditors for the benefit of such creditors, or takes any other action indicating an inability to meet its financial obligations as they become due.
